# What must NOT be uploaded to Vercel.
#
# `vercel deploy` uploads the WORKING TREE, not the last commit — an untracked
# file that is merely present ships to production. (That is how the events UI
# reached prod ahead of its migrations.) So exclusion is by this file, not by
# what happens to be committed.
#
# Deliberately a superset of .gitignore's runtime entries: depending on CLI
# version a .vercelignore can REPLACE .gitignore rather than add to it, and
# uploading node_modules or .env.local would be far worse than a redundant line.

node_modules
.next
out
build
.vercel
.env
.env*.local
*.tsbuildinfo

# ---- source data, not application code -------------------------------------
# Import INPUTS that were parsed into the database once (hat write-ups, stat
# spreadsheets). They contain members' names, emails and phone numbers, they are
# never read at build or run time, and they have no business on a web host.
hats/
reference/
*.xlsx
*.csv
*.docx
*.doc
*.dotx
*.rtf
